cs.CR, cs.AR, cs.SY, cs.SE, cs.HC 

The paper focuses on proposing new security mechanisms for low-cost devices that make use of DRAM. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves hardware design and implementation, which suggests categories such as cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the integration of the proposed mechanisms with current DDR memory modules, which suggests the category cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper mentions the ease of use and integration of the proposed mechanisms, which suggests the category cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
